KSP: 1.9.1 Windows

Problem: My game keeps crashing upon start up.

Mods Installed:

Astronomers Visual Pack 1.9.1
Chatterer 1.9.1
Community Tech Tree 1.9.1
EVE 1.9.1
EVA Struts 1.9.1
Hide Empty Tech Tree Nodes 1.6.9
KAS 1.9.1
KPBS 1.9.1
KIS 1.9.1
Modular Flight Integrator 1.8.9
Module Manager 4.1.3

Reproduction steps:

Crashes as soon as game opens.

Log: https://www.dropbox.com/s/21jqtpgvvhd62qa/KSP.log?dl=0

Edited June 8, 2020 by joynerm
updated log

MiniAVC is broken sincea bit back.

Remove all MiniAVC.dll or install ZeroMiniAVC

12 hours ago, Curveball Anders said:

MiniAVC is broken sincea bit back.

Remove all MiniAVC.dll or install ZeroMiniAVC

 

Okay so I did that and now everything loads in, however I'm having multiple errors in which items from mods "cannot be cloned because the item does not exist" and eve won't load in either. I updated the log, the same link should work. my image is an example of one of the errors.

6 minutes ago, joynerm said:

Okay so I did that and now everything loads in, however I'm having multiple errors in which items from mods "cannot be cloned because the item does not exist" and eve won't load in either. I updated the log, the same link should work. my image is an example of one of the errors.

That by itself isn't bad, just means that you have some MM patches which are looking for missing mods.

So. First you need to go through your installed mods and verify that ALL dependencies are installed.

Also, post a current log file so that others can help

14 hours ago, joynerm said:

my image is an example of one of the errors

The error messages in the image are normal for the main menu. Scatterer can't find Eve or any other planet because they don't exist in the start menu universe.

"DXT3 format is NOT supported. Use DXT5" means you won't be able to use the KerbalHacks parts unless the mod's textures are converted to DXT5 (you can possibly do that yourself with vector graphics software)
